FBIS4-35398 "drnes105_j_94010" FBIS-NES-94-105 Daily Report 31 May 1994 ARABIAN PENINSULA Yemen Roundup of North-South Fighting on 31 May Roundup of North-South Fighting on 31 May Aden Denies Clashes Near Lahijj EA3105203094 Aden Democratic Republic of Yemen Radio Network in Arabic 1800 GMT 31 May 94 EA3105203094 Aden Democratic Republic of Yemen Radio Network in Arabic 1800 GMT 31 May 94 Arabic BFN [Excerpt] A responsible source in the command of the Armed Forces of the Democratic Republic of Yemen has expressed astonishment and deep regret over what was reported by the media, quoting 'Abd-al-Qadir Ba Jammal, who shamelessely stated that the Sanaa regime's forces had drawn close to the Lahijj Governorate's supply of drinking water and was about to capture it. What concerns us here is to refute the report, which conflicts with the facts of battles being fought far away, toward the Tawr al-Bahah, al-Khattabiyyah, and al-Turbah areas, where our heroic forces have delivered crushing blows against the invading forces. [passage omitted]
